%% C4 dynamic — Long-running job invocation (contained goja job-runner)
%% Source of truth: docs/adr/ (ADR-0013) + docs/architecture-brief.md — regenerate via /c4-designer, do not hand-edit
%% Generated: 2026-07-12
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant SRV as byteswarm Server (plugin)
    participant JOB as byteswarm-job
    participant JOBSTORE as Job workdirs & logs
    participant TOOLS as External tools & processes
    participant NET as External network services

    SRV->>SRV: script plugin handles event, decides to run a long job
    SRV->>JOB: host.exec allowlisted runner: run --jobs-dir D <name> <args> [OS exec]
    Note over JOB: name resolved WITHIN jobs dir (pathguard: no abs, no ".."); args are UNTRUSTED
    JOB->>JOB: daemonize — setsid/re-exec, stdio to job log
    JOB-->>SRV: launcher exits 0 (host.exec returns within the plugin timeout)
    Note over SRV,JOB: triggering event is acked now — at-least-once no longer covers the detached work
    JOB->>JOBSTORE: create per-job workdir + open job log [filesystem]
    JOB->>JOB: run operator-authored JS on goja under a wall-clock watchdog
    opt host.exec(bin, argv, opts)
        JOB->>TOOLS: run command, unrestricted argv, bounded output [OS exec]
        TOOLS-->>JOB: stdout / stderr / exit code
    end
    opt host.fs / host.http
        JOB->>JOBSTORE: open file I/O (absolute or per-job workdir) [filesystem]
        JOB->>NET: HTTP(S) request, bounded body [network]
    end
    alt completes within wall-clock
        JOB->>SRV: host.publish completion, operator-local (0660 socket) [JSON over Unix domain socket]
    else timeout / uncaught error
        JOB->>JOB: watchdog interrupts VM; log bounded failure to job log
        JOB->>SRV: publish job_failed safety-net event [JSON over Unix domain socket]
    end
